Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Montessori education (http://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Montessori_education) is an educational approach developed by Italian physician and educator Maria Montessori and characterized by an emphasis on independence, freedom within limits, and respect for a child's natural psychological, physical, and social development.

At this point, it is not reported whether the 3 EHEC isolates are genetically related besides being acquired in the same school, although not necessarily in the same classroom. It is also important to know what the timeline of onset of illness was in the 3 cases and what potential contact there was between the cases, either directly or by eating the same foods. The incubation period of EHEC can be up to 10 days, longer than most other bacterial enteric pathogens, so the cases, even if related, could have occurred over as long as 20 days. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2921237,239.]
